Add to ~/.claude/settings.json to get a macOS notification when a background
agent finishes or needs input (new Notification hook events in 2.1.198):

{
  "hooks": {
    "Notification": [
      {
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "osascript -e 'display notification \"A background agent needs you\" with title \"Claude Code\"'"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}

Remove it with daily-diff rollback, or delete the block by hand.
